    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Looking at a way around this it looks like it wouldn't be possible to use the `data/values` provided by Algolia since it doesn't return all the possible values for numericAttributes:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"name\":\"startTimeEpoch\",\r\n    \"data\": {\r\n        \"1489581000\":139,\r\n        \"1489581060\":138,\r\n        \"1489581120\":143,\r\n        \"1489581180\":146,\r\n        \"1489581240\":136,\r\n        \"1489581300\":120,\r\n        \"1489581360\":129,\r\n        \"1489581420\":114,\r\n        \"1489581480\":86,\r\n        \"1489581540\":38,\r\n        \"1489585500\":28,\r\n        \"1489589400\":38,\r\n        \"1489722600\":28,\r\n        \"1489788000\":153,\r\n        \"1490997600\":92,\r\n        \"1491606000\":141,\r\n        \"1492250400\":111,\r\n        \"1506124800\":82,\r\n        \"1509145200\":51,\r\n        \"1510009200\":80\r\n    },\r\n    \"exhaustive\":true,\r\n    \"stats\": {\r\n        \"min\":1489543740,\r\n        \"max\":1510009200,\r\n        \"avg\":1490079779,\r\n        \"sum\":17624663633760\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince the list there is not an exact list containing every single `startTimeEpoch` in the index, I cannot use that to provide a more accurate list of days that are used.",
