    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @RyanTheAllmighty,\r\n\r\nYou're right, the `noRefinement` feature of the MultiRange was done with a different logic that the one you need. \r\n\r\nWhile we are thinking about this issue, maybe you can try those following workaround:\r\n\r\n1. You can create your own connector by reusing the MultiRange one, and just changing the logic.\r\n2. Maybe you could use the RefinementList instead. The RefinementList has a prop `transformItems` that can let you return an array that will contain days. And by increasing the limitMin, you can check if you have some date that falls in. \r\n\r\nWhat do you think? \r\n",
